      • lowpt

        public int lowpt(V v)
        Finds the lowpoint of a vertex The lowpoint of a vertex v, denoted by lowpt(v), is the lowest DFS index of an ancestor of v reachable through a back edge from a descendant of v
        Parameters:
        v - Vertex
        Returns:
        lowpt of v if there are back edges leading form descendant to ancestor of v, -1 otherwise

      • lowpts

        public int[] lowpts(V v)
        Finds both lowpt1 and lowpt2 of a vertex The lowpoint of a vertex v, denoted by lowpt(v), is the lowest DFS index of an ancestor of v reachable through a back edge from a descendant of v lowpt1 is the lowest index, lowpt2 is the second lowest
        Parameters:
        v - Vertex
        Returns:
        An array whose first element is lowpt1 and the second one is lowpt2
